If `j` equals to `puzzleLength - 1`, `j + 1` will be out of the string&#39;s bounds.

Your problem isn&#39;t really the code line:

    puzzleDup = puzzleDup.substring(j + 1, puzzleDup.length());

but rather the fact that you are iterating through the wrong Puzzle String at two specific locations (loops) within your code. Let&#39;s take the second ***inner*** FOR loop within the first set of Loops:

    for(j = 0; j &lt; puzzleLength; j++) {
